The plan is to collect useful snippets and code-examples to help creating and maintaining a pkm in Hugo (and posibly Logseq).
   Automating import  To import pages from logseq:
#!/usr/bin/env bash  BLOG=$HOME/Documents/QWxleA.github.io NOTES=$BLOG/content/notes ASSETS=&#34;$BLOG/content/notes/assets&#34; HUGOASSETS=$BLOG/static/assets  STARTPAGE=&#34;$NOTES/Start here.md&#34;  ZIP=$HOME/Downloads/publicExport.zip  explode() {  # rm $NOTES/*.md   unzip -o -d $NOTES $ZIP  if [ -d &#34;$ASSETS&#34; ]; then  for a in $ASSETS/*; do  mv &#34;$a&#34; $HUGOASSETS  done  rmdir &#34;$ASSETS&#34;  fi  # FIXME  if [ -f &#34;$STARTPAGE&#34; ]; then  mv &#34;$STARTPAGE&#34; &#34;$BLOG/content/_index.
